                            oc:textContent "`pip install git+https://github.com/wayneweiqiang/GaMMA.git`" ] ;
                    oc:sectionLevel 2 ;
                    oc:sectionOrder 2 ;
                    oc:sectionTitle "Installing GaMMA" ],
                [ a oc:Section ;
                    oc:hasContent [ a oc:Paragraph ;
                            oc:blockType "paragraph" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 3 ;
                            oc:textContent "`Zhu, W., McBrearty, I. W., Mousavi, S. M., Ellsworth, W. L., & Beroza, G. C. (2022). Earthquake phase association using a Bayesian Gaussian mixture model. Journal of Geophysical Research: Solid Earth, 127(5).`" ],
                        [ a oc:Paragraph ;
                            oc:blockType "paragraph" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 1 ;
                            oc:textContent "GaMMA is an earthquake phase association algorithm that treats association as an unsupervised clustering problem. It uses multivariate Gaussian distribution to model the collection of phase picks of an event, and uses Expectation-Maximization to carry out pick assignment and estimate source parameters i.e., earthquake location, origin time, and magnitude." ],
                        [ a oc:Paragraph ;
                            oc:blockType "paragraph" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 4 ;
                            oc:textContent "The skill is a derivative of the repo https://github.com/AI4EPS/GaMMA" ],
                        [ a oc:Paragraph ;
                            oc:blockType "paragraph" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 2 ;
                            oc:textContent "`GaMMA` is a python library implementing the algorithm. For the input earthquake traces, this library assumes P/S wave picks have already been extracted. We provide documentation of its core API." ] ;
                    oc:sectionLevel 2 ;
                    oc:sectionOrder 1 ;
                    oc:sectionTitle "What is GaMMA?" ] ;
            oc:sectionLevel 1 ;
            oc:sectionOrder 1 ;
