oc:kn_0f4f3132 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When preparing input data for association()" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Timestamps in the picks DataFrame must be in UTC. Phase types must be 'p' or 's' (lowercase). Picks with amp==0 or amp==-1 are filtered out when use_amplitude=True." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Non-UTC timestamps lead to incorrect travel-time calculations; non-lowercase phase types are internally forced but explicit correctness prevents edge cases." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_2a4d3540 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:KnownIssue ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When interpreting output events" ;
    oc:directiveContent "When use_amplitude=False, the magnitude field in output events is set to 999 (sentinel value). Events with fewer than min_picks_per_eq picks are discarded." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Using the sentinel magnitude value as a real measurement would corrupt downstream analysis. Filtered events may still appear in intermediate results." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_3b1f0a5e a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:OutputFormat ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Interpreting association() output" ;
    oc:directiveContent """events: list[dict] with keys: time, magnitude, sigma_time, sigma_amp, cov_time_amp, gamma_score, num_picks, num_p_picks, num_s_picks, event_index, x(km), y(km), z(km)
assignments: list[tuple(pick_index, event_index, gamma_score)]""" ;
    oc:templateVariables "assignments",
        "events" .

oc:kn_4194c0d1 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When configuring DBSCAN pre-clustering" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Estimate dbscan_eps using estimate_eps(stations, vp) for new networks, but practitioners often manually tune it to 10-15 seconds for specific regions after empirical testing." ;
    oc:hasRationale "The auto-estimated eps provides a reasonable starting point but network geometry and seismicity rate may require adjustment for optimal clustering." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_512e10a5 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Full GaMMA association workflow" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Prepare picks DataFrame (id, timestamp, type, prob, amp) ensuring UTC timestamps and lowercase phase types. 2. Prepare stations DataFrame (id, x(km), y(km), z(km)) with projected coordinates. 3. Verify id columns match between picks and stations. 4. Build config dict with required keys (dims, min_picks_per_eq, max_sigma11, use_amplitude, bfgs_bounds, oversample_factor). 5. Estimate dbscan_eps via estimate_eps() or set manually. 6. Call association(picks, stations, config, method='BGMM'). 7. Parse (events, assignments) output tuple." ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_595a3f3a a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When processing large continuous datasets" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use DBSCAN pre-clustering to reduce the problem size before running the full GMM association. Tune dbscan_min_samples and dbscan_min_cluster_size based on expected seismicity rate." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Without pre-clustering, the GMM must consider all picks simultaneously, which is computationally intractable for large datasets." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_5aa540dd a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When selecting the association method" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use BGMM (Bayesian Gaussian Mixture Model) method with oversample_factor=5.0 for robust association. Use GMM with oversample_factor=1.0 only for simpler cases." ;
    oc:hasRationale "BGMM provides better uncertainty quantification and is less prone to overfitting with sparse data." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_5ba09271 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When preparing station metadata and config" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Station coordinates must be in a projected local coordinate system (e.g., UTM via pyproj), not geographic lat/lon. The bfgs_bounds must match the projected coordinate ranges." ;
    oc:hasRationale "GaMMA performs distance calculations in km; geographic coordinates would produce incorrect spatial relationships." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_b0ed4fae a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Standard association workflow" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "python" ;
    oc:directiveContent """from gamma.utils import association, estimate_eps

config = {
    "dims": ["x(km)", "y(km)", "z(km)"],
    "use_amplitude": True,
    "vel": {"p": 6.0, "s": 3.47},
    "bfgs_bounds": ((x_min, x_max), (y_min, y_max), (z_min, z_max), (None, None)),
    "max_sigma11": 2.0,
    "min_picks_per_eq": 5,
    "oversample_factor": 5.0,
    "use_dbscan": True,
    "dbscan_eps": estimate_eps(stations, 6.0),
}
events, assignments = association(picks, stations, config, method="BGMM")""" .

oc:kn_b1209362 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before calling association()" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Picks DataFrame must contain columns: id, timestamp, type, prob, amp. Stations DataFrame must contain columns: id, x(km), y(km), z(km). The id columns must match between both DataFrames." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Mismatched or missing columns will cause runtime errors or silently incorrect association results." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_ecf2ccef a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Prerequisite ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before using this skill" ;
    oc:directiveContent "P/S wave phase picks must already be extracted from seismic traces before using GaMMA. GaMMA does not perform phase picking." ;
    oc:hasRationale "GaMMA only performs association; a separate phase picking tool (e.g., EqTransformer, PhaseNet via seisbench-model-api) is needed upstream." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_eee97e51 a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Estimating DBSCAN epsilon parameter" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "python" ;
    oc:directiveContent """from gamma.utils import estimate_eps
eps = estimate_eps(stations, vp, sigma=2.0)""" .

